example.para:
Notice how the angle brackets in the
	  #include line need to be referenced by
	  their entities instead of being included literally.

example.programlisting:
#include <stdio.h>

int
main(void)
{
    printf("hello, world\n");
    return 0;
}

#include <stdio.h> 

int 
main(void)
{
    printf("hello, world\n"); 
}

note.para:
Notice how the
	  &man.command.section;
	  notation is easier to follow.
